  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThe default host for the HTTP APIs is `127.0.0.1` but given the way docker networking works out of the box, this interface is not reachable from outside the container by default.\r\n\r\nI stumbled into this testing out the new (standard) HTTP APIs and it would be nice if there is some mention of it in the docs on running prysm inside a container.\r\n\r\nA suitable workaround is to run the HTTP APIs on `0.0.0.0` e.g.\r\n```bash\r\ndocker run -p 3501:3501 gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:stable --grpc-gateway-host 0.0.0.0\r\n```",
